        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/greg_mcclellan/{size}/3682_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-02-11T19:25:24.531Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I just opened this bottle a few nights ago. Same vintage. Actually my 7 year old picked it, my wife blinded me on it. I concluded that it was maybe a Beaune Pinot Noir, around 2016. I was so happy to be wrong. It was vibrant and energetic, everything I want in Gamay but seem to find less and less. Clearly they are keeping yields in check. Even that slight VA lift worked for me.</p>",
