        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote group-BerserkerBusiness\" data-username=\"Greg_McClellan\" data-post=\"6\" data-topic=\"288993\" data-full=\"true\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/greg_mcclellan/48/3682_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Greg_McClellan:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I just opened this bottle a few nights ago. Same vintage. Actually my 7 year old picked it, my wife blinded me on it. I concluded that it was maybe a Beaune Pinot Noir, around 2016. I was so happy to be wrong. It was vibrant and energetic, everything I want in Gamay but seem to find less and less. Clearly they are keeping yields in check. Even that slight VA lift worked for me.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Nice! I just had the 2019 Thivin C\u00f4te de Brouilly Chapelle magnum this week and it too had taken on a rather Burgundian character. A great wine.</p>",
